{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1592,"text":"[\"Rebecca Newberger Goldstein\"]"},{"time":4270,"text":"[\"Steven Pinker\"]"},{"time":6349,"text":"[\"The Long Reach of Reason\"]"},{"time":11348,"text":"Cabbie: Twenty-two dollars.\nSteven Pinker: Okay."},{"time":17857,"text":"Rebecca Newberger Goldstein: Reason \nappears to have fallen on hard times:"},{"time":21975,"text":"Popular culture plumbs new depths of dumbth"},{"time":25310,"text":"and political discourse has become a race"},{"time":27776,"text":"to the bottom."},{"time":30791,"text":"We're living in an era of scientific creationism,"},{"time":35345,"text":"9/11 conspiracy theories, psychic hotlines,"},{"time":39359,"text":"and a resurgence of religious fundamentalism."},{"time":42466,"text":"People who think too well"},{"time":44520,"text":"are often accused of elitism,"},{"time":46876,"text":"and even in the academy,"},{"time":49035,"text":"there are attacks on logocentrism,"},{"time":51684,"text":"the crime of letting logic dominate our thinking."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56569,"text":"SP: But is this necessarily a bad thing?"},{"time":59076,"text":"Perhaps reason is overrated."},{"time":61295,"text":"Many pundits have argued that a good heart"},{"time":63438,"text":"and steadfast moral clarity"},{"time":65388,"text":"are superior to triangulations\nof overeducated policy wonks,"},{"time":69626,"text":"like the best and brightest and that dragged us"},{"time":72291,"text":"into the quagmire of Vietnam."},{"time":74153,"text":"And wasn't it reason that gave us the means"},{"time":75975,"text":"to despoil the planet"},{"time":77705,"text":"and threaten our species with\nweapons of mass destruction?"},{"time":80726,"text":"In this way of thinking, \nit's character and conscience,"},{"time":83965,"text":"not cold-hearted calculation, that will save us."},{"time":87091,"text":"Besides, a human being is not a brain on a stick."},{"time":90956,"text":"My fellow psychologists have shown that we're led"},{"time":93474,"text":"by our bodies and our emotions"},{"time":95375,"text":"and use our puny powers of reason"},{"time":97360,"text":"merely to rationalize our gut feelings after the fact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100720,"text":"RNG: How could a reasoned\nargument logically entail"},{"time":103917,"text":"the ineffectiveness of reasoned arguments?"},{"time":107349,"text":"Look, you're trying to persuade\nus of reason's impotence."},{"time":111185,"text":"You're not threatening us or bribing us,"},{"time":113572,"text":"suggesting that we resolve the issue"},{"time":115203,"text":"with a show of hands or a beauty contest."},{"time":118411,"text":"By the very act of trying to\nreason us into your position,"},{"time":122348,"text":"you're conceding reason's potency."},{"time":125366,"text":"Reason isn't up for grabs here. It can't be."},{"time":128372,"text":"You show up for that debate"},{"time":129770,"text":"and you've already lost it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132612,"text":"SP: But can reason lead us in directions"},{"time":135327,"text":"that are good or decent or moral?"},{"time":137999,"text":"After all, you pointed out that reason"},{"time":140510,"text":"is just a means to an end,"},{"time":142284,"text":"and the end depends on the reasoner's passions."},{"time":144750,"text":"Reason can lay out a road\nmap to peace and harmony"},{"time":147317,"text":"if the reasoner wants peace and harmony,"},{"time":149173,"text":"but it can also lay out a road\nmap to conflict and strife"},{"time":152000,"text":"if the reasoner delights in conflict and strife."},{"time":154677,"text":"Can reason force the reasoner to want"},{"time":157003,"text":"less cruelty and waste?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159312,"text":"RNG: All on its own, the answer is no,"},{"time":162584,"text":"but it doesn't take much to switch it to yes."},{"time":165345,"text":"You need two conditions:"},{"time":167699,"text":"The first is that reasoners all care"},{"time":170258,"text":"about their own well-being."},{"time":171968,"text":"That's one of the passions that has to be present"},{"time":174864,"text":"in order for reason to go to work,"},{"time":177068,"text":"and it's obviously present in all of us."},{"time":178956,"text":"We all care passionately"},{"time":181486,"text":"about our own well-being."},{"time":183750,"text":"The second condition is that reasoners"},{"time":185583,"text":"are members of a community of reasoners"},{"time":188068,"text":"who can affect one another's well-being,"},{"time":190142,"text":"can exchange messages,"},{"time":191655,"text":"and comprehend each other's reasoning."},{"time":194483,"text":"And that's certainly true of our gregarious"},{"time":197469,"text":"and loquatious species,"},{"time":199481,"text":"well endowed with the instinct for language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202337,"text":"SP: Well, that sounds good in theory,"},{"time":204659,"text":"but has it worked that way in practice?"},{"time":206673,"text":"In particular, can it explain"},{"time":208507,"text":"a momentous historical development"},{"time":210438,"text":"that I spoke about five years ago here at TED?"},{"time":213305,"text":"Namely, we seem to be getting more humane."},{"time":215950,"text":"Centuries ago, our ancestors would burn cats alive"},{"time":219310,"text":"as a form of popular entertainment."},{"time":221570,"text":"Knights waged constant war on each other"},{"time":223449,"text":"by trying to kill as many of each\nother's peasants as possible."},{"time":226615,"text":"Governments executed people for frivolous reasons,"},{"time":229290,"text":"like stealing a cabbage"},{"time":230700,"text":"or criticizing the royal garden."},{"time":232948,"text":"The executions were designed to be as prolonged"},{"time":235201,"text":"and as painful as possible, like crucifixion,"},{"time":238139,"text":"disembowelment, breaking on the wheel."},{"time":240233,"text":"Respectable people kept slaves."},{"time":242299,"text":"For all our flaws, we have abandoned"},{"time":244272,"text":"these barbaric practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245765,"text":"RNG: So, do you think it's\nhuman nature that's changed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248533,"text":"SP: Not exactly. I think we still harbor instincts"},{"time":251318,"text":"that can erupt in violence,"},{"time":252917,"text":"like greed, tribalism, revenge, dominance, sadism."},{"time":257287,"text":"But we also have instincts that can steer us away,"},{"time":260286,"text":"like self-control, empathy, a sense of fairness,"},{"time":263778,"text":"what Abraham Lincoln called"},{"time":265054,"text":"the better angels of our nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266643,"text":"RNG: So if human nature didn't change,"},{"time":268685,"text":"what invigorated those better angels?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270684,"text":"SP: Well, among other things,"},{"time":272217,"text":"our circle of empathy expanded."},{"time":274359,"text":"Years ago, our ancestors would feel the pain"},{"time":276806,"text":"only of their family and people in their village."},{"time":279279,"text":"But with the expansion of literacy and travel,"},{"time":282081,"text":"people started to sympathize"},{"time":284007,"text":"with wider and wider circles,"},{"time":285672,"text":"the clan, the tribe, the nation, the race,"},{"time":288553,"text":"and perhaps eventually, all of humanity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291508,"text":"RNG: Can hard-headed scientists"},{"time":293714,"text":"really give so much credit to soft-hearted empathy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296735,"text":"SP: They can and do."},{"time":298416,"text":"Neurophysiologists have found neurons in the brain"},{"time":300417,"text":"that respond to other people's actions"},{"time":302597,"text":"the same way they respond to our own."},{"time":304664,"text":"Empathy emerges early in life,"},{"time":306391,"text":"perhaps before the age of one."},{"time":308274,"text":"Books on empathy have become bestsellers,"},{"time":309917,"text":"like \"The Empathic Civilization\""},{"time":311931,"text":"and \"The Age of Empathy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":314111,"text":"RNG: I'm all for empathy. I mean, who isn't?"},{"time":316809,"text":"But all on its own, it's a feeble instrument"},{"time":320477,"text":"for making moral progress."},{"time":322347,"text":"For one thing, it's innately biased"},{"time":324534,"text":"toward blood relations, babies"},{"time":326660,"text":"and warm, fuzzy animals."},{"time":328494,"text":"As far as empathy is concerned,"},{"time":330893,"text":"ugly outsiders can go to hell."},{"time":334426,"text":"And even our best attempts to work up sympathy"},{"time":337829,"text":"for those who are unconnected with us"},{"time":339813,"text":"fall miserably short, a sad truth about human nature"},{"time":344012,"text":"that was pointed out by Adam Smith."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346566,"text":"Adam Smith: Let us suppose that the great empire"},{"time":348347,"text":"of China was suddenly swallowed\nup by an earthquake,"},{"time":350962,"text":"and let us consider how a \nman of humanity in Europe"},{"time":353552,"text":"would react on receiving intelligence"},{"time":355254,"text":"of this dreadful calamity."},{"time":357317,"text":"He would, I imagine, first of all express very strongly"},{"time":359534,"text":"his sorrow for the misfortune of that unhappy people."},{"time":362194,"text":"He would make many melancholy reflections"},{"time":364071,"text":"upon the precariousness of human life,"},{"time":366261,"text":"and when all these humane sentiments"},{"time":368275,"text":"had been once fairly expressed,"},{"time":370118,"text":"he would pursue his business or his pleasure"},{"time":372370,"text":"with the same ease and tranquility"},{"time":374519,"text":"as if no such accident had happened."},{"time":376611,"text":"If he was to lose his little finger tomorrow,"},{"time":379153,"text":"he would not sleep tonight,"},{"time":380690,"text":"but provided he never saw them,"},{"time":382432,"text":"he would snore with the most profound security"},{"time":384870,"text":"over the ruin of a hundred million of his brethren."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387779,"text":"SP: But if empathy wasn't enough\nto make us more humane,"},{"time":390682,"text":"what else was there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":392242,"text":"RNG: Well, you didn't mention what might be"},{"time":394936,"text":"one of our most effective better angels: reason."},{"time":398762,"text":"Reason has muscle."},{"time":401330,"text":"It's reason that provides the push to widen"},{"time":404704,"text":"that circle of empathy."},{"time":406849,"text":"Every one of the humanitarian developments"},{"time":409757,"text":"that you mentioned originated with thinkers"},{"time":412355,"text":"who gave reasons for why some practice"},{"time":415225,"text":"was indefensible."},{"time":417183,"text":"They demonstrated that the way people treated"},{"time":419822,"text":"some particular group of others"},{"time":421769,"text":"was logically inconsistent"},{"time":423555,"text":"with the way they insisted\non being treated themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426127,"text":"SP: Are you saying that reason"},{"time":427821,"text":"can actually change people's minds?"},{"time":430127,"text":"Don't people just stick with whatever conviction"},{"time":432057,"text":"serves their interests"},{"time":433538,"text":"or conforms to the culture that they grew up in?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436354,"text":"RNG: Here's a fascinating fact about us:"},{"time":439513,"text":"Contradictions bother us,"},{"time":441591,"text":"at least when we're forced to confront them,"},{"time":443726,"text":"which is just another way of saying"},{"time":445544,"text":"that we are susceptible to reason."},{"time":448290,"text":"And if you look at the history of moral progress,"},{"time":451121,"text":"you can trace a direct pathway\nfrom reasoned arguments"},{"time":454828,"text":"to changes in the way that we actually feel."},{"time":458167,"text":"Time and again, a thinker would lay out an argument"},{"time":461748,"text":"as to why some practice was indefensible,"},{"time":465018,"text":"irrational, inconsistent with values already held."},{"time":470067,"text":"Their essay would go viral,"},{"time":472135,"text":"get translated into many languages,"},{"time":474420,"text":"get debated at pubs and coffee houses and salons,"},{"time":477770,"text":"and at dinner parties,"},{"time":479377,"text":"and influence leaders, legislators,"},{"time":483430,"text":"popular opinion."},{"time":484968,"text":"Eventually their conclusions get absorbed"},{"time":488221,"text":"into the common sense of decency,"},{"time":490548,"text":"erasing the tracks of the original argument"},{"time":493237,"text":"that had gotten us there."},{"time":495045,"text":"Few of us today feel any need to put forth"},{"time":497842,"text":"a rigorous philosophical argument"},{"time":499950,"text":"as to why slavery is wrong"},{"time":502209,"text":"or public hangings or beating children."},{"time":505767,"text":"By now, these things just feel wrong."},{"time":508667,"text":"But just those arguments had to be made,"},{"time":511504,"text":"and they were, in centuries past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514253,"text":"SP: Are you saying that people needed"},{"time":516005,"text":"a step-by-step argument to grasp"},{"time":518053,"text":"why something might be a wee bit wrong"},{"time":520112,"text":"with burning heretics at the stake?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":521890,"text":"RNG: Oh, they did. Here's the French theologian"},{"time":524807,"text":"Sebastian Castellio making the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527729,"text":"Sebastian Castellio: Calvin says that he's certain,"},{"time":529744,"text":"and other sects say that they are."},{"time":531384,"text":"Who shall be judge?"},{"time":532657,"text":"If the matter is certain, to whom is it so? To Calvin?"},{"time":535095,"text":"But then, why does he write so\nmany books about manifest truth?"},{"time":538114,"text":"In view of the uncertainty, we must define heretics"},{"time":540650,"text":"simply as one with whom we disagree."},{"time":542414,"text":"And if then we are going to kill heretics,"},{"time":544386,"text":"the logical outcome will be a war of extermination,"},{"time":546627,"text":"since each is sure of himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548498,"text":"SP: Or with hideous punishments"},{"time":550047,"text":"like breaking on the wheel?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":551890,"text":"RNG: The prohibition in our constitution"},{"time":554398,"text":"of cruel and unusual punishments"},{"time":556430,"text":"was a response to a pamphlet circulated in 1764"},{"time":560011,"text":"by the Italian jurist Cesare Beccaria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563530,"text":"Cesare Beccaria: As punishments\nbecome more cruel,"},{"time":565881,"text":"the minds of men, which like fluids"},{"time":567964,"text":"always adjust to the level of the objects"},{"time":569923,"text":"that surround them, become hardened,"},{"time":571802,"text":"and after a hundred years of cruel punishments,"},{"time":574647,"text":"breaking on the wheel causes no more fear"},{"time":576839,"text":"than imprisonment previously did."},{"time":578983,"text":"For a punishment to achieve its objective,"},{"time":581030,"text":"it is only necessary that the harm that it inflicts"},{"time":583770,"text":"outweighs the benefit that derives from the crime,"},{"time":586829,"text":"and into this calculation ought to be factored"},{"time":588937,"text":"the certainty of punishment"},{"time":590603,"text":"and the loss of the good"},{"time":591741,"text":"that the commission of the crime will produce."},{"time":594376,"text":"Everything beyond this is superfluous,"},{"time":596168,"text":"and therefore tyrannical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598119,"text":"SP: But surely antiwar movements depended"},{"time":600469,"text":"on mass demonstrations"},{"time":601998,"text":"and catchy tunes by folk singers"},{"time":604080,"text":"and wrenching photographs\nof the human costs of war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606987,"text":"RNG: No doubt, but modern anti-war movements"},{"time":610165,"text":"reach back to a long chain of thinkers"},{"time":612858,"text":"who had argued as to why we ought to mobilize"},{"time":615446,"text":"our emotions against war,"},{"time":617685,"text":"such as the father of modernity, Erasmus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620812,"text":"Erasmus: The advantages derived from peace"},{"time":622669,"text":"diffuse themselves far and wide,"},{"time":624334,"text":"and reach great numbers,"},{"time":626233,"text":"while in war, if anything turns out happily,"},{"time":628234,"text":"the advantage redounds only to a few,"},{"time":630458,"text":"and those unworthy of reaping it."},{"time":632469,"text":"One man's safety is owing\nto the destruction of another."},{"time":635346,"text":"One man's prize is derived\nfrom the plunder of another."},{"time":638015,"text":"The cause of rejoicings made by one side"},{"time":640182,"text":"is to the other a cause of mourning."},{"time":642530,"text":"Whatever is unfortunate in war,"},{"time":644071,"text":"is severely so indeed,"},{"time":645731,"text":"and whatever, on the contrary,"},{"time":647133,"text":"is called good fortune,"},{"time":648422,"text":"is a savage and a cruel good fortune,"},{"time":650341,"text":"an ungenerous happiness deriving\nits existence from another's woe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653978,"text":"SP: But everyone knows that the movement"},{"time":655835,"text":"to abolish slavery depended on faith and emotion."},{"time":659053,"text":"It was a movement spearheaded by the Quakers,"},{"time":661303,"text":"and it only became popular when\nHarriet Beecher Stowe's novel"},{"time":664638,"text":"\"Uncle Tom's Cabin\" became a bestseller."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666922,"text":"RNG: But the ball got rolling a century before."},{"time":669839,"text":"John Locke bucked the tide of millennia"},{"time":673077,"text":"that had regarded the practice as perfectly natural."},{"time":676502,"text":"He argued that it was inconsistent"},{"time":679076,"text":"with the principles of rational government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680998,"text":"John Locke: Freedom of men under government"},{"time":682643,"text":"is to have a standing rule to live by"},{"time":684662,"text":"common to everyone of that society"},{"time":686715,"text":"and made by the legislative power erected in it,"},{"time":689787,"text":"a liberty to follow my own will in all things"},{"time":691971,"text":"where that rule prescribes not,"},{"time":693691,"text":"not to be subject to the inconstant,"},{"time":695602,"text":"uncertain, unknown, arbitrary will of another man,"},{"time":699009,"text":"as freedom of nature is to\nbe under no other restraint"},{"time":701608,"text":"but the law of nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703558,"text":"SP: Those words sound familiar."},{"time":705350,"text":"Where have I read them before? Ah, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708076,"text":"Mary Astell: If absolute sovereignty \nbe not necessary"},{"time":710819,"text":"in a state, how comes it to be so in a family?"},{"time":713431,"text":"Or if in a family, why not in a state?"},{"time":716411,"text":"Since no reason can be alleged for the one"},{"time":718279,"text":"that will not hold more strongly for the other,"},{"time":720387,"text":"if all men are born free,"},{"time":721820,"text":"how is it that all women are born slaves,"},{"time":724209,"text":"as they must be if being subjected"},{"time":726637,"text":"to the inconstant, uncertain,"},{"time":728675,"text":"unknown, arbitrary will of men"},{"time":731195,"text":"be the perfect condition of slavery?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734095,"text":"RNG: That sort of co-option"},{"time":736028,"text":"is all in the job description of reason."},{"time":738594,"text":"One movement for the expansion of rights"},{"time":740769,"text":"inspires another because the logic is the same,"},{"time":744659,"text":"and once that's hammered home,"},{"time":746558,"text":"it becomes increasingly uncomfortable"},{"time":749092,"text":"to ignore the inconsistency."},{"time":751286,"text":"In the 1960s, the Civil Rights Movement"},{"time":754081,"text":"inspired the movements for women's rights,"},{"time":755999,"text":"children's rights, gay rights and even animal rights."},{"time":759622,"text":"But fully two centuries before,"},{"time":762044,"text":"the Enlightenment thinker Jeremy Bentham"},{"time":764192,"text":"had exposed the indefensibility"},{"time":766894,"text":"of customary practices such as"},{"time":769336,"text":"the cruelty to animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771439,"text":"Jeremy Bentham: The question\nis not, can they reason,"},{"time":773819,"text":"nor can they talk, but can they suffer?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777212,"text":"RNG: And the persecution of homosexuals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780056,"text":"JB: As to any primary mischief,"},{"time":782024,"text":"it's evident that it produces no pain in anyone."},{"time":785281,"text":"On the contrary, it produces pleasure."},{"time":787531,"text":"The partners are both willing."},{"time":789061,"text":"If either of them be unwilling,"},{"time":790605,"text":"the act is an offense,"},{"time":791963,"text":"totally different in its nature of effects."},{"time":794172,"text":"It's a personal injury. It's a kind of rape."},{"time":796784,"text":"As to the any danger exclusive of pain,"},{"time":799028,"text":"the danger, if any, much consist"},{"time":800740,"text":"in the tendency of the example."},{"time":802579,"text":"But what is the tendency of this example?"},{"time":805713,"text":"To dispose others to engage in the same practices."},{"time":807985,"text":"But this practice produces not pain of any kind"},{"time":810679,"text":"to anyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812313,"text":"SP: Still, in every case, it took at least a century"},{"time":814779,"text":"for the arguments of these great thinkers"},{"time":816638,"text":"to trickle down and infiltrate\nthe population as a whole."},{"time":820043,"text":"It kind of makes you wonder about our own time."},{"time":822522,"text":"Are there practices that we engage in"},{"time":824491,"text":"where the arguments against\nthem are there for all to see"},{"time":827286,"text":"but nonetheless we persist in them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829575,"text":"RNG: When our great grandchildren look back at us,"},{"time":832567,"text":"will they be as appalled by some of our practices"},{"time":835782,"text":"as we are by our slave-owning, heretic-burning,"},{"time":839441,"text":"wife-beating, gay-bashing ancestors?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":842529,"text":"SP: I'm sure everyone here\ncould think of an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845321,"text":"RNG: I opt for the mistreatment of animals"},{"time":847351,"text":"in factory farms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849062,"text":"SP: The imprisonment of nonviolent drug offenders"},{"time":851292,"text":"and the toleration of rape in our nation's prisons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853994,"text":"RNG: Scrimping on donations to life-saving charities"},{"time":856719,"text":"in the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858376,"text":"SP: The possession of nuclear weapons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860718,"text":"RNG: The appeal to religion to justify"},{"time":863095,"text":"the otherwise unjustifiable,"},{"time":864735,"text":"such as the ban on contraception."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867247,"text":"SP: What about religious faith in general?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869035,"text":"RNG: Eh, I'm not holding my breath."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871216,"text":"SP: Still, I have become convinced"},{"time":873273,"text":"that reason is a better angel"},{"time":874984,"text":"that deserves the greatest credit"},{"time":876556,"text":"for the moral progress our species has enjoyed"},{"time":879210,"text":"and that holds out the greatest hope"},{"time":881325,"text":"for continuing moral progress in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884141,"text":"RNG: And if, our friends,"},{"time":886043,"text":"you detect a flaw in this argument,"},{"time":888723,"text":"just remember you'll be depending on reason"},{"time":892045,"text":"to point it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893416,"text":"Thank you.\nSP: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896130,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}